%description:
TCP Fast Open (RFC 7413) F5.1: client-side active blackhole detection and
disable timer (fastopenBlackholeTimeout), three connections through the same
client/server Tcp modules:
 - Connection 1 (port 1000): primes the client's cookie cache (bare
   cookie-request SYN, as in tcp_fastopen_1.test).
 - Connection 2 (port 1001): a deferred SYN+data attempt using the cached
   cookie. Its first two transmissions (the original send and its first
   SYN-REXMIT) are dropped by the tcptester script; on the second REXMIT,
   syn_rexmit_count reaches TFO_BLACKHOLE_RTO_THRESHOLD (2) with
   fastopenSynDataLen>0, tripping recordFastOpenBlackhole() -- confirmed via
   its EV_INFO line. This same (now undropped) retransmission still carries
   the cookie and data: blackhole detection disables *future* connection
   attempts, not the one that tripped it.
 - Connection 3 (port 1002), opened well within the 60s disable window: even
   though a cookie is still cached, isActiveFastOpenDisabled() makes this
   connection behave exactly like "no cookie cached" -- a bare, dataless SYN
   carrying an empty cookie-request option, not the real cached cookie.

Falsification: building this test caught a real bug -- the first version of
the isActiveFastOpenDisabled() gate was added directly to
writeHeaderOptions()'s cookie lookup, which (correctly) suppressed
connection 3's stale cookie, but ALSO suppressed connection 2's OWN
already-in-flight retransmission's cookie option (since blackhole detection
trips *during* that same retransmission's processing, before
writeHeaderOptions() runs for it) -- producing a nonsensical wire segment
carrying 200 bytes of SYN data with no Fast Open option at all. Fixed by
gating on state->fastopenCookieRequestPending (set once, at connect() time,
by process_OPEN_ACTIVE, and left false for an already-deferred connection's
retransmissions) instead of re-deriving disablement independently inside
writeHeaderOptions(). This test's exact wire assertions for both connection
2's successful retransmission (cookie AND data present) and connection 3's
suppressed attempt (neither present) would fail again if either regressed.

%inifile: omnetpp.ini
[General]
record-vector-results = false
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib
sim-time-limit = 30s

network = inet.test.moduletest.lib.TcpTestNet1

cmdenv-event-banners=false
cmdenv-express-mode=false
cmdenv-log-prefix="[%c]: "

*.testing=false
*.tcptester.script="a3 delete;a4 delete"

*.cli_app.localAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.cli_app.localPort=1000
*.cli_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.cli_app.connectPort=2000
*.cli_app.active=true
*.cli_app.tOpen=0s
*.cli_app.tSend=-1s
*.cli_app.sendBytes=0B
*.cli_app.tClose=-1s
*.cli_app.sendScript=""
*.cli_app.fastOpen=true
*.cli_app.active2=true
*.cli_app.tOpen2=1s
*.cli_app.localPort2=1001
*.cli_app.tSend2=1s
*.cli_app.sendBytes2=200B
*.cli_app.fastOpen2=true
*.cli_app.active3=true
*.cli_app.tOpen3=20s
*.cli_app.localPort3=1002
*.cli_app.tSend3=20s
*.cli_app.sendBytes3=200B
*.cli_app.fastOpen3=true

*.srv_app.localAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.srv_app.localPort=2000
*.srv_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.srv_app.connectPort=1000
*.srv_app.active=false
*.srv_app.tOpen=0s
*.srv_app.tSend=-1s
*.srv_app.sendBytes=0B
*.srv_app.tClose=-1s
*.srv_app.sendScript=""
*.srv_app.active2=false
*.srv_app.tOpen2=1s
*.srv_app.localPort2=2000
*.srv_app.active3=false
*.srv_app.tOpen3=20s
*.srv_app.localPort3=2000

*.*_tcp.sackSupport = false
*.*_tcp.windowScalingSupport = false
*.*_tcp.timestampSupport = false
*.*_tcp.mss = 1000
*.*_tcp.tcpAlgorithmClass = "TcpReno"

*.cli_tcp.fastopenClientEnabled = true
*.cli_tcp.fastopenBlackholeTimeout = 60s
*.srv_tcp.fastopenServerEnabled = true
*.srv_tcp.fastopenLenientCookieValidation = false

include ../../lib/tcp-legacy.ini

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: postrun.pl
open FILE, '<test.out';
while($sor = <FILE>)
{
    if ($sor =~ /^\[testing\]: (.*)$/)
    {
        print "$1\n";
    }
}
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command:  perl ./postrun.pl
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Connection 2's first two transmissions (original + 1st REXMIT) are dropped by the tester.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[1.001 A003] A.1001 > B.2000: S 250000:250200(200) win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize NOP NOP FastOpen(cookieLen=8)# deleting
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[4.001 A004] A.1001 > B.2000: S 250000:250200(200) win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize NOP NOP FastOpen(cookieLen=8)# deleting
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Connection 2's 2nd REXMIT (syn_rexmit_count reaches the blackhole threshold here, but this
%# transmission itself still carries the cookie+data -- blackhole detection disables FUTURE
%# attempts, not the in-flight one that tripped it) gets through and accelerates normally.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[10.001 A005] A.1001 > B.2000: S 250000:250200(200) win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize NOP NOP FastOpen(cookieLen=8)
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[10.003 B002] A.1001 < B.2000: A S 2500500:2500500(0) ack 250201 win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# The blackhole was recorded exactly once (2nd REXMIT), disabling active TFO for 60s (until t=70).
%contains: stdout
Fast Open: disabling active TFO after suspected blackhole (count=1, until t=70)
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Connection 3, opened at t=20s (well within the t=70 disable window): despite a cookie still
%# being cached, this SYN is bare/dataless with an EMPTY cookie-request option -- not the real
%# cached cookie -- exactly matching "no cookie cached" behavior.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[20.001 A007] A.1002 > B.2000: S 5000000:5000000(0) win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize NOP NOP FastOpen(cookieLen=0)
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
